    "Below, Table 1 summarizes recent (2020-2024) papers on LVRT techniques for DFIG wind turbines: Subsynchronous resonanceTo understand the phenomenon of SSR, consider a turbine generator connected to a series capacitor-compensated transmission system, as shown in Fig. 1, with an electrical resonant frequency determined by Eq.",
    "( 1).where, f er < f o, f o is the rated frequency, X c is the reactance of the series capacitor, and X t is the total reactance of the generator, transformer, and transmission line.",
    "At resonant frequency f er, the positive sequence components of armature current produce magnetic field which tends to induce rotor currents at a frequency f r = f o -f er The induced rotor currents generate armature voltage components at Subsyn- chronous frequency which may cause Subsynchronous armature currents [37] [38].",
    "The Subsynchronous frequency current may produces a negative damping torque.",
    "Subsynchronous current's negative dampening impact can eventually result in the failure of the generator shaft [39,40]."
